doc.ContractDescription: FLOOD REGIMES AND CARBON CYCLINGIN ANTHROPOGENIC LANDSCAPES OF THE BOLIVIAN AMAZON WE PROPOSE A 3 YEAR MULTIDISCIPLINARY INVESTIGATION OF THE HYDROLOGY WITHIN PRE COLUMBIAN ANTHROPOGENIC LANDSCAPES OF AMAZONIA AND THEIR IMPLICATIONS FOR PAST AND PRESENT GLOBAL CHANGE, ENVIRONMENTAL CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT, AND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT. OUR PROPOSAL FOCUSES ON THE IMPACT OF PRE COLUMBIAN EARTHWORKS ON THE HYDROLOGY OF SAVANNAS AND WETLANDS IN BOLIVIA. LANDSCAPE ARCHAEOLOGY AND HISTORICAL ECOLOGY ARE FRAMEWORKS TO UNDERSTAND HOW 1, NATIVE PEOPLES TRANSFORMED THEIR ENVIRONMENT, 2, ENGINEERED LANDSCAPES IMPACT BIODIVERSITY, AGRODIVERSITY, ECOLOGICAL HETEROGENEITY, AND SUSTAINABLE LAND USE, AND 3, LANDSCAPES WITH DEEP HUMAN HISTORY CAN CONTRIBUTE TO CONTEMPORARY CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT. AMAZONIA WAS HISTORICALLY CONSIDERED TO BE OF LIMITED POTENTIAL FOR HUMANS. SCHOLARS THEREFORE ASSUMED THAT SIMPLE SOCIO POLITICAL ORGANIZATION, MOBILE LIFEWAYS, AND SUBSISTENCE BASED ON HUNTING, GATHERING, FISHING, AND SMALL SCALE FARMING CHARACTERISTIC OF THE HISTORIC PERIOD, ADEQUATELY REFLECTED PRE COLUMBIAN CONDITIONS. THE DISCOVERY OF RAISED FIELDS, CAUSEWAYS, CANALS, FISH WEIRS, RESERVOIRS, DIKES, MOUNDS AND OTHER EARTHWORKS THROUGHOUT THE BOLIVIAN AMAZON CHALLENGED THIS PERSPECTIVE, AS PRE COLUMBIAN SOCIETIES BUILT A LANDSCAPE THAT SUPPORTED A COMPLEX CULTURE IN A CURRENTLY UNDERPOPULATED AND ECONOMICALLY DEPRESSED AREA. THE PAST INHABITANTS BUILT ELABORATE EARTHWORKS FOR CONTROLLING, WHICH SUSTAINED INTENSIVE AGRICULTURE, FISHERIES, AND DENSE HUMAN SETTLEMENT, AND IN SOME CASES, HIGH BIODIVERSITY. OUR PROJECT PROPOSES TO MAP THE SEASONAL DYNAMICS OF REGIONAL FLOODING OVER MULTIPLE YEARS AND HOW NATIVE PEOPLES MANAGED WATER AND AQUATIC RESOURCES THROUGH EARTHWORKS. MAPPING PROTOCOLS ARE BASED ON REMOTE SENSING OF IMAGERY FROM NASA AND OTHER INSTITUTIONS TO FACILITATE COMPUTER MODELING AND TEMPORAL SIMULATION OF COMPLEX, DYNAMIC LANDSCAPES. GIS AND REMOTE SENSING WILL BE VERIFIED USING PREVIOUS ARCHAEOLOGICAL, ECOLOGICAL, AND PEDOLOGICAL RESEARCH WITHIN THE REGION. PRINCIPLE GOALS INCLUDE 1, CONSTRUCTING A DETAILED DEM FOR LOCAL AND REGIONAL HYDROLOGY, 2, DEFINING SOURCES, PROCESSES, AND VARIATION OF SEASONAL FLOODING, 3, MAPPING AND MODELING WATER FLOW BEFORE, DURING, AND AFTER ANNUAL FLOODING, 4, DETECTING AND DOCUMENTING PRE-COLUMBIAN EARTHWORKS FROM REMOTE SENSING, COMBINED WITH PREDICTIVE MODELING BASED ON THE SIGNATURES OF KNOWN EARTHWORKS, 5, DEFINING, MODELING, AND INTERPRETING PRE COLUMBIAN ANTHROPOGENIC LANDSCAPE TRANSFORMATION, AND 6, EVALUATING POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE IMPACTS OF HUMAN ACTIVITIES OVER TIME ON LOCAL AND REGIONAL HYDRAULIC PATTERNS THROUGH EXPERIMENTAL RECONSTRUCTION OF PRE COLUMBIAN EARTHWORKS. THIS RESEARCH WILL PROVIDE A FOUNDATION FOR FUTURE MODELING OF CARBON PRODUCTION, FLOW, CYCLING, SEQUESTRATION, AND LOSS WITHIN ANTHROPOGENIC LANDSCAPES.

doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROJECT WILL CONDUCT INNOVATIVE RESEARCH TO IMPLEMENT A SUSTAINABLE AND EXTENSIBLE VISION FOR SPACE EXPLORATION IN THE LONG TERM, SPECIFICALLY IN SUPPORT OFTHE ETDP (EXPLORATION TECHNOLOGY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM) WITHIN ESMD (EXPLORATION SYSTEMS MISSION DIRECTORATE). ONE FUNDAMENTAL PROBLEM IS THAT SINCE THE BEGINNING OFTHE SPACE AGE, THE BARRIERS TO THE EXPLORATION OFSPACE HAVE REMAINED UNNECESSARILY HIGH. THUS, THE CONTINUED HIGH COST OF ACCESS TO SPACE HAS INHIBITED THE SPHERE OF ECONOMIC ACTIVITY FROM EXPANDING INTO ORBIT, AS IT ONCE DID FROM LAND TO SEA, AND IT HAS STALLED SPACE EXPLORATION GENERALLY, LEADING TO A DECREASE IN THE TOTAL NUMBER OF ANNUAL LAUNCHES AND SPACE MISSIONS FROM THE LATE 19605 UNTIL TODAY. IF THERE IS TO BE A SIGNIFICANT INCREASE IN THE QUALITY AND FREQUENCY OFSPACE EXPLORATION MISSIONS WITHOUT SIGNIFICANT GOVERNMENT FUNDING INCREASES, THEN IMPROVEMENTS IN THE EOST AND SIMPLICITY OF SPACE EXPLORATION TECHNOLOGY ARE PREREQUISITES. A FORTHCOMING NATIONAL ACADEMY OF SCIENCES (NAS) RCVLEW FINDS THAT LONGER-TERM INVESTMENTS IN SPACE TECHNOLOGY ARE NEEDED TO ENABLE THE LATER PHASES OFTHE VISION FOR SPACE EXPLORATION (VSE). TO RECTIFY THIS, THE NAS COMMITTEE RECOMMENDS THAT "TO MEET LONGER-TENN TECHNOLOGY NEEDS, THE COMMITTEE RECOMMENDS THAT THE ETDP SEED LOWER TRL CONCEPTS THAT TARGET SUSTAINABILITY AND EXTENSIBILITY TO LONG-TERM LUNAR AND MARS MISSIONS, THUS OPENING THE TRL PIPELINE, RE-ENGAGING THE ACADEMIC COMMUNITY, AND BEGINNING TO BUILD IN THE INNOVATION IN TECHNOLOGY DEVELOPMENT THAT WILL BE NECESSARY TO COMPLETE THE VSE." THE SEEDS OF THE SOLUTIONS ALREADY EXIST: 1 1/2 LOW-COST LAUNCH SYSTEMS ARE ENABLED BY THERMAL ROCKETS. WHILE THE NAS REPORT IDENTIFIES THE ABSENCE OF NUCLEAR THERMAL ROCKETS, WE PROPOSE TO DEVELOP MICROWAVE THERMAL ROCKETS; A NON-NUCLEAR ADAPTATION WITH GREATER PERFORMANCE AND LOWER COST. TO REDUCE THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCTION COSTS OF SPACECRAFTS, WE WILL UNDERTAKE RESEARCH TO SHORTEN THE CYCLE OF SPACE MISSION DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION (A MAJOR FACTOR IN THE SPACECRAFT COSTS) USING ADVANCED APPROACHES TO END-TO-END LOW-EOST SMALL SPACECRAFT MISSION DESIGN, INTEGRATION AND LAUNCH. RESEARCH WILL ALSO BE UNDERTAKEN IN EVA (EXTRA VEHICULAR ACTIVITIES) SYSTEM TECHNOLOGIES; AN AREA GIVEN A YELLOW FLAG IN THE RECENT REVIEW OF NASAS EXPLORATION TECHNOLOGY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM CONDUCTE4 BY NATIONAL RESEARCH COUNCILS (NRC) AERONAUTICS AND SPACE ENGINEERING BOARD. FINALLY, UNIQUE LONG-RUN CLLOMETRLC RESEARCH (I.E. APPLICATION OFECONOMIC THEORY, ECONOMETRIC TECHNIQUES, AND OTHER FORMALLMATHEMATICAL METHODS) WLL1 BE UNDERTAKEN INTO THE ECONOMICS MD POLITICS OF SPACE EXPLORATION PROGRAMS. THE OBJECTIVE OFTHIS EFFORT IS TO IDENTIFY POTENTIAL FUNDING SOURCES AND VEHICLES SUITABLE FOR PUBLIC-PTIVATE PARTNERSHIPS, WHICH ARE AN AVENUE TO POTENTIALLY REALIZE THE VSE MAY BE REALIZED IN THE LONG TERM. THIS PROPOSED MULTIDISCIPLINARY PROGRAM ATTACKS THESE DIFFERENT BUT INTERLINKED PROBLEMS SIMULTANEOUSLY, WITH AN EMPHASIS ON CROSS-FERTILIZATION OF TRANSFORMATIONAL IDEAS AND APPROACHES THAT ARE MUTUALLY SUPPORTING ACROSS DIFFERENT DISCIPLINES. THE PROJECT WILL ALSO INCLUDE THE PURSUIT OF COMMERCIAL OPPORTUNITIES THAT LEVERAGE THE RESEARCH UNDERTAKEN TO ENABLE SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT OFTHE TECHNOLOGIES IDENTIFIED.
